#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.44:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.44:0.2"
msgid "5. Sāmaññavagga"
msgstr "5. Similarity"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.44:0.3"
msgid "44. Paññāvimuttasutta"
msgstr "44. Freed by Wisdom"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.44:1.1"
msgid "“‘Paññāvimutto, paññāvimutto’ti, āvuso, vuccati."
msgstr "“Reverend, they speak of a person called ‘freed by wisdom’."

msgctxt "an9.44:1.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, paññāvimutto vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "What is the one freed by wisdom that the Buddha spoke of?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.44:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati, "
msgstr ""
"“First, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures … enters "
"and remains in the first absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.44:2.2"
msgid "paññāya ca naṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "And they understand that with wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.44:2.3"
msgid "Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, paññāvimutto vutto bhagavatā pariyāyena … pe …."
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the one freed by wisdom in a qualified "
"sense. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.453"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.44:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā "
"parikkhīṇā honti, "
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation "
"of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements "
"come to an end. "

msgctxt "an9.44:3.2"
msgid "paññāya ca naṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "And they understand that with wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.44:3.3"
msgid "Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, paññāvimutto vutto bhagavatā nippariyāyenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the one freed by wisdom in a definitive "
"sense.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.44:3.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
